senses.sense_text:
A location first mentioned at Jdg.21.8; 
referred to as Jabesh (יָבֵשׁ), or Jabesh/-gilead (NIV= Jabesh Gilead) (יָבֵשׁ גִּלְעָד). § a town in the territory of Gilead; according to Eusebius, it is beyond the Jordan, 6 miles (10 km) from Pella, on the mountain road to Gerasa
may be modern 'Wadi Yabes'

A man from the tribe of Benjamin living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.8.12; 
only referred to as Shemed (שָׁ֫מֶד); 
son of Elpaal; 
a brother of Eber, Misham, Beriah, Shema, Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, Ishmerai, Izliah and Jobab. §a Benjamite, son of Elpaal and builder of the towns of Ono and Lod
